{
  "texts": [
    "To demonstrate our proposed architecture, we experimented with a benchmark dataset of CXR images, one of the most frequently downloaded datasets for testing on Kaggle.",
    "Using these studies and datasets for binary classification.",
    "Python 3.7, Anaconda/3, and CUDA/10 are installed on a Windows server with an i5 CPU, 2 GB GPU, and 8 GB RAM, as well as an Anaconda/3 distribution.",
    "In addition to the parameters listed above, the",
    "Python libraries Pytorch, OpenCV, matplotlib, os, math, and NumPy are used."
  ]
}